TITLE: Retrieval-Augmented Generation Robustness Survey
AUTHORS: Sharma
YEAR: 2025
TYPE: arxiv
VENUE: arXiv
EVIDENCE: method_paper
CITATIONS: 12
REPLICATION: 6400
RELEVANCE: 9300
CLAIM: Retrieval-augmented generation reduces dependence on parametric memory by conditioning generation on external evidence.
CLAIM: RAG introduces challenges in retrieval quality, grounding fidelity, efficiency, and noisy or adversarial inputs.
METHOD: Survey taxonomy over retriever-centric, generator-centric, hybrid and robustness-oriented systems.
LIMITATION: RAG faithfulness depends on retrieved evidence quality and pipeline coordination.
